post_text: A little history on our wonderful community!
shared_text:
Ron Stein‚ÄéWatertown, SD memories
June 25 at 9:13 AM ¬∑

Salute to Small towns in Codington County: FLORENCE:...A mere 17 miles to the NW of Watertown on Hwy 20 is the home of 374 friendly folks. Originally plated as a town on the Minneapolis & St Louis Railroad line in 1906, it is still going strong long after the railroad has left. I remember Florence as a young boy when my Dad and Uncles took us to the sloughs nearby to learn how to duck hunt. There was a bar on Main street where we always stopped for pop and candy. Nearby Grass Lake was always a good place to hunt, although it is now a place to fish. Most of us have probably driven past Florence on our way to Webster or Aberdeen. Please click through 11 pictures.

post_text:
Good afternoon,

Here is a reminder for our drop off days on Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday

The drop off days will go from 4:00-6:00 pm on W, Th, Fr. Wednesday will be dedicated to high school, Thursday to middle school, and Friday to elementary. If you have students in various grades, you can pick which ones work best. We ask that HS and MS students come on those days to drop off materials and address any items that come up. Elementary parents can bring their students or take care of it on their own. We will have teachers available on the dedicated days to answer any questions that students have.

Students need to bring any missing homework for turn in, textbooks, library books, laptops, chargers, jerseys, and any other items they may have at home. Students will enter on the east door into the commons and get checked out at each table. they will then exit the main doors on the south side of the gym when they are finished.

With any missing or damaged items, a bill will be sent out.

We look forward to seeing the students one last time before summer break.

Take care

March 6 at 4:26 PM ¬∑

DSU CEO is excited to congratulate the 20 finalists in the 2020 DSU High School Business Plan Competition! We saw some tremendous business ideas and plans and had difficulty narrowing down the list to only 20 but we are thrilled to have them on campus March 28 for the live elevator pitch competition and a chance to win the top prize of $1,000.

The finalists come from Florence, Sully Buttes, Northwestern, Arlington, Brandon Valley, Eureka, and Belle Fourche high schools. There are some tremendous teachers in this state doing some tremendous work. Thank you one and all!

post_text: On Sunday, December 8th the Florence Community was able to enjoy horse drawn wagon rides and a visit with Santa and Mrs. Claus at the Florence Country School House Museum!
